    <div class="container">
        <h1> CSS Positioning Techniques</h1>

        <div class="box static-box">
            <strong>Static Positioning:</strong> A default positioning which is positioned according to the normal document fow.
        </div>

        <div class="box relative-box">
            <strong>Relative Positioning:</strong> Positioned relative to its normal position, 20px from the top and left.
        </div>
<div class="absolute-box-container">
            <strong>Absolute Positioning Container:</strong> This container holds an absolutely positioned box.
            <div class="absolute-box">
                <strong>Absolute Positioning:</strong> Positioned relative to the nearest positioned ancestor (the container).
            </div>
        </div>
<div class="fixed-box">
            <strong>Fixed Positioning:</strong> It remains fixed to the top-right corner even when we do scrolling.
        </div>

<div class="box sticky-box">
            <strong>Sticky Positioning:</strong> It gets fixed at the top of the screen when we scroll past it.
        </div>

